<Layout title="Vibe Coding with Gemini | Ela Sobol">
  <article style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 5rem 2rem; line-height: 1.8; color: #2c3e50;">
    <h1 style="font-size: 3rem; color: #1565c0; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Vibe Coding: Bridging the Gap Between AI Efficiency and Human Creativity</h1>
    <p style="color: #666; margin-bottom: 3rem;">Published March 6, 2026 • 4 min read</p>

    <p>
      I’m excited to share that I just finished building my personal portfolio site! But instead of spending weeks wrestling with CSS syntax, I utilized <strong>Gemini 3 Flash</strong> to "vibe code" the entire project in <strong>Astro</strong>.
    </p>

    <h2 style="color: #2e7d32;">What is "Vibe Coding"?</h2>
    <p>
      In the world of Data Science, we often talk about the technical "how." Vibe coding shifts the focus to the "what." By describing my vision—soft blue/pink palettes, side-by-side hero sections, and mobile-responsive grids—I was able to collaborate with Gemini 3 Flash to generate clean, modular code in real-time.
    </p>

    <div style="background: #e3f2fd; padding: 2rem; border-radius: 15px; margin: 2rem 0; border-left: 5px solid #1565c0;">
      <p style="margin: 0; font-style: italic;">
        "It wasn't about the AI doing the work for me; it was about the AI acting as a bridge between my psychological design goals and the technical execution."
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 style="color: #2e7d32;">The Process</h2>
    <p>
      We started with a basic text-only site and iterated. I would describe a feeling—"make it look more professional yet likeable"—and Gemini would provide the CSS flexbox logic to make it happen. 
      This is the intersection of AI and Psychology that I am so passionate about: utilizing tools to handle the "efficiency" so I can focus on the "creativity" and the human experience of the site.
    </p>

    <h2 style="color: #2e7d32;">Takeaways</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>AI is a Collaborator:</strong> It’s a pair programmer that never gets tired of adjusting "blush pink" hex codes.</li>
      <li><strong>Focus on Intent:</strong> When the barrier to entry (syntax) is lowered, the quality of the intent becomes the most important factor.</li>
      <li><strong>Human-Centric Tech:</strong> Even in a world of LLMs, the personality (and the cats!) are what make a site meaningful.</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="margin-top: 3rem; font-weight: bold; color: #1565c0;">
      I’d love to hear your thoughts—are you using AI to speed up your creative workflows? Let’s connect! 
    </p>

